### loadYAML() {#af96a5f4033bb285a8570b073578aceb1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error CallSiteInfoLoader::loadYAML (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> YAMLFile)</>}>
This method reads the specified YAML file, parses its content, and updates the <code>Funcs</code> vector with call site information based on the YAML data.

<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="Funcs">A reference to a vector of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/gsym/functioninfo">FunctionInfo</a> objects to be populated.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="YAMLFile">A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> representing the path to the YAML file to be loaded.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
An <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/error">llvm::Error</a></code> indicating success or describing any issues encountered during the loading process.
</SectionUser>
